Log / Entry:PRO REAL-TIME LOG / 2398735Category:ANITAAction:CoordinationFlags:No Flag
Author:Mills, Andrew D.COL's ECOS-OPS checked in with Marshall PRO on IPPLCALL said they are ready for ANITA activities on the timeline and was there if we had any questions. I let him know we have no questions at this time and that we have an ANITA Specialist arriving ~ 10:40. Notified OC.

I was not familiar with this position so I did some research. Pulled from ESA's website:
  • European Astronaut Centre Crew Operations Support centre (ECOS)
  • ECOS runs and implements European payloads on the International Space Station in the fields of space medicine, space training and crew systems.
  • The main tasks of this operations centre are the flight procedures development and the preparation, integration and execution of different research activities, technology demonstrations and system activities.
  • In addition, ECOS takes care of the Mission Operation Implementation Concept (MOIC) and the collection of in-flight data. To perform all these activities, ECOS receives the inputs of developers and scientists.

Reference IFN 160011 for ANITA Operations Responsibility Matrix

MERLIN3 - Citations: Chit 020938, EFN109974A, OCR MERLIN-0052, PPCR 2728, PRO Log 2397166
Background: MERLIN3 was powered off and MTL cooling terminated after what the PD strongly suspects is a Disk On Chip (DOC) failure on GMT 363. Recovery needs to be performed ASAP to support CS return science on SpX-24.

Big Picture: While troubleshooting is being performed (MERLIN-DOC-T/S PT1 on FE-6 at 10:35, PLUTO's Troubleshooting in EFN 109974A, and MERLIN-DOC-T/S PT2 on FE-6 at 12:15), MERLIN3 needs to be activated in AAA mode. If troubleshooting is successful, we will configure MERLIN3 for MTL cooling by deactivating it in AAA mode and activating it in MTL mode, and finally MERLIN PD will perform MERLIN3-DNLK-CMD. If troubleshooting is unsuccessful, we will deactivate MERLIN3 in AAA mode, abort our nominal MERLIN3 activation, and schedule slide 2 of the one-time PPO from OCR MERLIN-0052 at a later date (PPMs have it scheduled for GMT 011 at the moment).

Added to the timeline on GMT 006 from slide 1 of the one-time PPO in OCR MERLIN-0052:
  • PRO-MRL3 AAA ACT-CMD (006/10:05) - GCP Vol. 3 Ann. 2 3.6.5 MERLIN 3 ACTIVATION Scenario 1
  • PRO-MRL3 AAA DCT-CMD (006/11:35) - GCP Vol. 3 Ann. 2 3.6.6 MERLIN 3 DEACTIVATION Scenario 1
  • PRO-MRLN3 ACT-CMD (006/12:05) - GCP Vol. 3 Ann. 2 3.6.5 MERLIN 3 ACTIVATION Scenario 3 (Execute if JOY or Abort if NO JOY)
Depending on whether or not crew and PLUTO's troubleshooting is successful or not, we will either:
  • If successful, deactivate MERLIN3 in AAA Mode (PRO-MRL3 AAA DCT-CMD at 11:35) and activating it again with MTL cooling (PRO-MRLN3 ACT-CMD 12:05 FLAT's ER5 FAA commanding will be added by JPLAN).
OR
  • If unsuccessful, deactivate MERLIN3 in AAA Mode (PRO-MRL3 AAA DCT-CMD at 11:35), aborting the activation with MTL cooling (PRO-MRLN3 ACT-CMD 12:05).
FIR/FBCE - Citations: OCR FIRCIR-0264, PPCR 2728, OCR FIRCIR-0263, PRO Log 2395756, PRO Log 2398738, OC Log 2398723, OC Log 2398559, PRO Log 2398382

Author:Wall, Kellen L.EXPRESS Rack 6 Troubleshooting

Summary: After Cold Stowage had issues downlinking their files, ER6 seemed to have other rack functionality not working. RIC Reboot did not recover functionality, and we narrowed it down to an issue with MRT. DMC updated the PEHG software yesterday, and we can no longer point ER6 MRT through the Internal Gateway. From DMC:
ER6 PEHG was upgraded to PEHG software v3 on GMT 2022/005 which converted its gateway from unicast gateway to multicast gateway, so the Internal Gateway IP address that we previously used is no longer valid. MRT will now be routed through the External Gateway to PEHG 2.

Per Vol 3 Ann 3 GCP 7.3.1, we need to notify ECOSTRESS for their forward actions.
Per Vol 3 Ann 3 GCP 7.4.1, we need to notify GEDI for their forward actions.
OC will contact the PDs.
OC brought up FR B19-70 Payload Actions for JEM-EF ATCS Loss of Flow
Checked with FLAT, they state their pump has stopped.
Received a Teams message from Amy Jupin that both ECOSTRESS and GEDI safed themselves, that's why they lost H&S, and OCO-3 will lose H&S in about an hour or so.0
Looking at our Power Data sheets (Adam and I working together on this still).
PDUb1 RPC1 tripped, which supports JEF PDBb, which supports Main Power for GEDI/ECOSTRESS as well as SPBb. SPBb RPC8 is the RPC that is the keep alive power for EFU2. Our suspicion is that CANSEI may have commanded to that, which may have caused the issue we are now having.
Could not get a straight answer from CANSEI (language barrier/kept misinterpreting the question). It is OFF due to the the trip.
Tried again to ask CANSEI if this RPC was closed prior to PDUb1 RPC 1 trip. They state is was OPEN and was not commanded closed at any time.
After discussing with OC/POD/PRO1, we thought perhaps we could get CANSEI to open Main power both ECOSTRESS and GEDI as they still indicate GREEN (powered) thought the PDUb1 RPC1 is tripped. CANSEI stated they cannot command to that and that the power is OFF. The hope was to get GEDI and ECOSTRESS to autosafe.

02:05 - J-Flight reported to Flight they are in the process of recovering their ATCS system. CANSEI also confirmed this with PRO.
Per FR B19-18 - No impacts for GEDI/ECOSTRESS since heater power is still on. No thermal clock. NREP has no heater power, per CANSEI/Operational was already OPEN, thus the FR states that heater power will need to be powered back on for about 1 hour prior to operational power being applied.
02:23 - J-Flight reports they have lost cooling loop A again and will need 30 mins to recover again.

Ashley Kincade called the PRO console and stated that around the time STP-H8 sent a command that eventually caused a power uptick on EFU12 (NRT that Adam ran), power started being pulled from EFU12 (which is around the time we had the RPC trip and loss of ATCS in the JEM.

CANSEI has submitted IFN 160235 (STP H8 Current value on GMT2022/008). Have notified POD/Externals Lead. Apparently both RPC 13 and RPC 30 had power when JEF PDB b trip OFF. Now rev'd to A, as had CANSEI add POD/OC/POI Specialist.

Lots of forward work to go. JAXA ATCS cooling being recovered, PDUb1 RPC1 trip, STP-H8 activated though power on both Main RPCs from EFU2 and EFU12. STP-H8 may not be culprit but something is pulling power from EFU 12.

Handover: POD brought to the team about the consideration of once STP-H8 is complete and active (pretty much there, to consider having JAXA remove EFU12 main power from STP-H8 (since it is backup power), then have JAXA close RPC. If no trip, that is good. Then we would have JAXA close the EFU12 main power, and see if we get the JEM PDUb1 RPC1 trip again. Just some thoughts POD had with oncoming POD/kind of isolating where the problem may lie. POD also discussed with STP-H8 PD on this plan.

Log / Entry:PRO REAL-TIME LOG / 2400106Category:MELFI 3Action:MDE CMDFlags:MELFI Ops Lead
Author:Parks, Floyd A.MELFI-3 MDE Command Validity Status (MELFI3-SW-0007 - Withdrawn) MDE Command Validity Status
Similar to PAR (MELFI3-SW-0005 - Withdrawn) MELFI 3 Temporary MDE Command Parity Failure

16:47:07 - MELFI-3 MELFI MDE Command validity Status - Out of State
16:47:08 - MELFI-3 MELFI MDE Command validity Status - OK

Just for cognizance, why it happens;
MDE Command Validity Status = 0 if a valid MDE command has not been transmitted since the last H&S Packet. MDE monitors to receive the motor speed setup every second, even though no change in speed is requested by the motor algorithm.

Since the crew accessed MELFI 3, motor speed increased due to warmup (which the MDE motor algorithm should be actively monitoring to limit power consumption). A motor speed setup NOT sent within the 1 second margin should trigger the MDE Command Validity Status EM.

As long as the motor speed setup is received again and MDE command validity status comes back in limits, this signature should be a non-issue corrected by the MDE motor algorithm.

Reference MELFI SW Users Manual (MELFI-MA-03000-0436-MMT)
